    "_CMCC_Summary": "NTWF Workflow Ontology from Jessica Talisman's Ontology Series. Role-agent separation, PROV-O provenance chains, Dublin Core metadata, all three agent types working together in cross-departmental workflows.",
    "_competency_questions": {
      "CQ1": "What are all the steps in a workflow, and in what order? -> WorkflowSteps by IsStepOf, order by SequencePosition",
      "CQ2": "Who is responsible for approving production deployment? -> step-release-approval.AssignedRole -> role-release-manager.FilledBy -> agent-maria-gonzalez",
      "CQ3": "Which steps require human vs AI/automated? -> Filter WorkflowSteps by RequiresHumanApproval",
      "CQ4": "What artifacts does each step produce, and lineage? -> Artifacts.GeneratedBy, Artifacts.DerivedFrom chain",
      "CQ5": "Which workflows haven't been reviewed in 12 months? -> Filter Workflows by Modified < today - 12mo",
      "CQ6": "Delegation chain? -> Roles.DelegatesTo: Release Manager -> VP Engineering -> CTO",
      "CQ7": "Which workflows involve Engineering and Legal? -> production-deployment has steps owned by both",
      "CQ8": "What datasets does QBR consume? -> step-data-collection, step-metrics-analysis, step-financial-review ConsumesDataset"
    },
    "_conversion_metadata": {
      "source": "Jessica Talisman Ontology Series Parts I-III",
      "table_count": 10
    }
